&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Baca Saw Operator – Construction Resources Surfaces (Decatur, GA)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Construction Resources Surfaces is seeking a dependable, detail‑oriented individual to join our production team as a &lt;strong&gt;Baca Saw Operator&lt;/strong&gt;. This role involves working with automated cutting equipment to support the fabrication of stone and surface materials used in residential and commercial projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate and monitor a robotic cutting system equipped with a rotating saw&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow production schedules and job specifications to ensure accurate material processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with preparing materials before cutting and organizing finished pieces afterward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform basic equipment checks and communicate any issues to the supervisor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, safe, and organized work area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support general shop operations as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferably &lt;strong&gt;2–3 years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; in fabrication, manufacturing, or machine operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn and operate automated or computer‑assisted machinery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a fast‑paced, industrial environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and willingness to follow established procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable attendance and a team‑oriented mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;This position is based in our Decatur, Georgia facility and involves hands‑on work with stone materials and production equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#CRTrades&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;BENEFITS&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Medical&lt;br&gt;Dental&lt;br&gt;Vision&lt;br&gt;Employer Paid Basic Employee Life and AD&amp;amp;D Insurance&lt;br&gt;Employer Paid Long Term Disability&lt;br&gt;Flexible Spending Accounts&lt;br&gt;Voluntary&amp;nbsp;Short-Term Disability&lt;br&gt;Voluntary Life and AD&amp;amp;D Insurance&lt;br&gt;Voluntary Accident&amp;nbsp;Insurance&lt;br&gt;Voluntary Critical Illness&amp;nbsp;Insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;EEO&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Construction Resources, our people are the driving force behind everything we do. Construction Resources is an equal opportunity employer that aspires to be the best in the business by building an associate experience that celebrates growth, development, and purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;PHYSICAL DEMANDS&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to speak or hear. The employee is frequently required to sit for extended periods of time, stand, walk, climb stairs, use hands to finger, handle or feel, and reach with hands and arms. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, distance vision, color vision, peripheral vision, depth perception and ability to adjust focus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;POSITION TYPE/EXPECTED HOURS OF WORK&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a full-time position that requires overtime as business needs dictate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;OTHER DUTIES&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Please note: &amp;nbsp;this job description is not designed to cover or contain a c

&lt;p&gt;At Construction Resources and its affiliated companies, we are more than a distributor—we are a trusted partner to designers, builders, remodelers, and homeowners. For over 50 years, we’ve delivered integrated solutions that help turn ideas into reality across residential, multi-family, and commercial projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our success is built on collaboration, craftsmanship, and a commitment to excellence. Whether you contribute on the design floor, in operations, or in the field, you’ll be part of a dedicated team that values people, quality, and continuous growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our affiliated brands include Cancos, UMI/Opustone, and Bell Cabinetry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY/OBJECTIVE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The Cabinet Designer is responsible for creating functional, aesthetically pleasing cabinet designs that meet customer needs while aligning with company standards and project requirements. This role works closely with customers, sales representatives, builders, contractors, and internal teams to develop customized cabinetry solutions, prepare design layouts, and ensure a seamless experience from concept through project completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet with customers to understand project goals, design preferences, budget, and functional requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design kitchen, bath, and other cabinetry layouts using industry-standard design software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare detailed drawings, renderings, specifications, and material selections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend cabinetry products, finishes, hardware, and accessories that align with customer needs and project budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review plans and measurements to ensure design accuracy and feasibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate quotes, proposals, and product specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales, Project Managers, Installers, and vendors to ensure successful project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Revise designs based on customer feedback and project changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate customer records, design files, and project documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on cabinetry trends, design styles, building codes, and product offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support customers throughout the design and selection process while delivering exceptional customer service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with showroom merchandising and product displays as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Qualifications&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s or Bachelor&#39;s degree in Interior Design, Architecture, or a related field preferred; equivalent experience will be considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of cabinet design, kitchen and bath design, or related experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cabinet design software such as 2020 Design, Cabinet Vision, ProKitchen, or similar programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of cabinetry construction, materials, and installation processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret blueprints, floor plans, and construction drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong mathematical and spatial reasoning skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational, communication, and customer service skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented with strong problem-solving abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Template Technician – Surfaces / Natural Stone&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Classification:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Non-Exempt, Hourly&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Reports to: &lt;/strong&gt;Template Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary / Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is responsible for creating accurate templates for the fabrication and installation of quartz, granite, and other natural stone countertops, as well as solid surface materials. The Template Technician ensures precise measurements and clear documentation to support successful production and installation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create accurate templates in accordance with job specifications and department procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform field measurements at residential and/or commercial job sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize templating methods including laser templating systems and/or traditional (manual/stick) templating techniques&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load, transport, and maintain templating tools and materials required for daily assignments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read and interpret architectural drawings, layouts, and technical documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with Order Control, Sales, fabrication teams, and customers regarding template details and scheduling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure proper maintenance and care of templating equipment and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, and safe work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competencies / Skills / Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in countertop templating, installation, fabrication, or related field preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with quartz, granite, or stone products strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with either laser templating equipment or traditional templating methods is acceptable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and understand basic drawings and job specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage time effectively and work in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and customer-facing skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn and be trained on company templating systems and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior industry experience preferred but not required; candidates with related construction, carpentry, or installation backgrounds encouraged to apply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to train candidates with transferable skills and a strong work ethic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supervisory Responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position has no supervisory responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role operates in both field (job site) and manufacturing environments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Demands&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly required to stand, walk, bend, and use hands and arms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift and/or move up to 50 pounds frequently, occasionally up to 75 pounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to perform physical tasks in job site and shop environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Type / Expected Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full-time position; schedule may vary based on business needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;stron

