&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt; Construction Resources is a premier provider of high-end building materials and interior home products, renowned for our dedication to quality and innovation. Our design centers are celebrated for their sophisticated product offerings and exceptional customer service. We are seeking talented Design Center Consultants to join our team and provide outstanding guidance and support to our clients as they navigate their projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt; The Design Center Consultant will play a crucial role in delivering an exceptional customer experience by leveraging product knowledge and offering personalized guidance. This role involves understanding clients&#39; project needs, providing expert recommendations, and ensuring a seamless connection to specialized experts within the showroom to facilitate the successful completion of their projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Experience Management:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver personalized and high-touch customer service by engaging with clients, understanding their project requirements, and offering tailored product recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a welcoming and informative atmosphere in the design center, addressing client inquiries and providing comprehensive product knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Consultation:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with clients to understand their design vision, preferences, and project requirements, and provide expert guidance to achieve their goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share insights on current design trends and innovative solutions to enhance the clients’ project outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in consultative selling to help clients understand CR’s full portfolio of product offerings and the opportunity to source all their products from a single vendor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expert Coordination:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate introductions and coordinate consultations with specialized product experts within the design center, ensuring clients receive in-depth assistance for specific product categories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule meetings or follow-ups with experts to support the smooth progression of client projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Guidance:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a thorough understanding of our product range, including tile, flooring, plumbing fixtures, countertops, and more, to provide clients with advice and solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer explanations of product features, benefits, and applications to help clients make informed decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Showroom Presentation and Support:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the design center is organized, with up-to-date product displays and a visually appealing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the showroom team with maintaining high standards of visual merchandising and support promotional activities as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Follow-Up and Relationship Building:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct follow-ups with clients to ensure their needs are met and their experience in the design center was exceptional.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong client relationships to encourage repeat business and referrals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep accurate records of client interactions, product selections, and project details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support inventory management and ensure product information is current and accessible.

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Centralized Estimating &amp;amp; Quoting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Director, Centralized Estimating &amp;amp; Quoting &lt;/strong&gt;is responsible for building and leading a centralized function that provides estimating and quoting support across Construction Resources’ business units and product categories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will establish standardized processes, improve quote speed and accuracy, and enhance the overall effectiveness of the sales organization. The Director will lead a high-performing team focused on delivering timely, high-quality quotes to support field sales teams, who in turn set expectations with end customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires a strong sense of urgency, deep understanding of construction and finished goods, and the ability to leverage systems, automation, and emerging technologies to drive scalable solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is critical to enabling scalable growth by transforming how Construction Resources delivers quoting and estimating support—driving speed, accuracy, and consistency across a decentralized sales organization. The Director will partner closely with Sales leadership on pricing strategy, margin integrity, and quote governance to ensure alignment with business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Centralized Quoting &amp;amp; Estimating Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, lead, and scale a centralized quoting and estimating function supporting all markets and categories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the development of standardized quoting processes to drive consistency, efficiency, and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate delivery of estimates and quotes aligned with sales and customer expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and continuously improve service levels for quote turnaround and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales leadership on pricing governance, margin expectations, and approval frameworks to ensure quotes align with company objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Support &amp;amp; Customer Responsiveness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support field sales teams as the primary internal customer, recognizing their role in setting expectations with the end customer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate with a high sense of urgency to meet tight timelines and customer commitments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and remove bottlenecks that impact the speed and effectiveness of the sales cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong alignment with Sales leadership to support revenue growth and execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technology &amp;amp; Process Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement systems, tools, and automation to improve quoting efficiency and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and introduce advanced solutions, including AI-driven tools, to enhance estimating accuracy and throughput&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with IT and business leaders on system enhancements and integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous process improvement initiatives across the quoting lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Sales, Operations, Sourcing, and Production teams to ensure feasibility, timing, and alignment on quotes&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY/OBJECTIVE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;This position will be responsible for the proper fabrication and assembling of metal parts and structures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabricate and assemble metal parts and structures according to technical drawings and quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Loads and logs materials onto truck and documents returned materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to read templates as per job specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drill and install all hardware accurately as per job specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attach all necessary hardware correctly as per job specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect finished products for accuracy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a well-organized, clean and safe work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned by management in support of initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competencies/Skills/Abilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical or vocational training in metal fabrication, welding or machining&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 to 3 years of experience in metal fabrication or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task and work within specified timeframes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast paced, self-directed environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current Forklift certification required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to problem-solve a plus&lt;/li&gt;
