&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Starting wage is based on a number of factors including, but not limited to, the position being offered, location, education, training, and/or experience. Construction Resources offers additional competitive and non-financial benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Stone Installer will contribute to the successful completion of both interior and exterior construction projects, ensuring a high standard of craftsmanship and client satisfaction. The Stone Installer will be responsible for the precise and aesthetically pleasing installation of various stone materials, including natural stone, tiles, and masonry products.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;Key Performance Indicators:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metal Preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface Preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grouting and Sealing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repair and Restoration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety Compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure, cut, and shape stones using hand or power tools to fit specific project requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare surfaces for stone installation by cleaning, leveling, and ensuring proper substrate conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply adhesive between stones and seal surfaces as needed for enhanced durability and appearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install all types of stone materials, including natural stone, tiles, and masonry products, in both interior and exterior spaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate alignment, spacing, and leveling of stones to achieve the desired aesthetic and structural outcome.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and repair damaged or chipped stones as needed during the installation process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform restoration work on existing stone installations to maintain their integrity and appearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough inspections of completed stone installations to ensure adherence to project specifications and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promptly address any defects or issues to meet client expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to safety protocols and guidelines, including the proper use of personal protective equipment and safe handling of tools and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with other construction professionals, including architects, designers, and project managers, to achieve project goals.&lt;/li&gt;
